description:
#shorts
Sports players and Hollywood actors have all been called heroes. But are they the real heroes? Weve seen a cultural shift in naming as heroes our medical professionals, grocery store workers and social workers. Could we finally be seeing that character is what makes a real hero? 

Sam Neves talks with Gary Blanchard about the impact this has on our cross-generational church and how this shift is helping us respect and honor each other more deeply.

Discover more about how Heroes 2: The Bible Trivia Game is working to bring people together to discover who the real heroes are we should be looking up to.

Learn more at: https://www.heroesbibletrivia.org/en/
